# Frontend table standards

## Rule: every table MUST use the shared design tokens

All data tables must share identical font size, row height, and sticky-cell
backgrounds.  The reference look is the catalog-products / advertising
products table.  Any new table that deviates will feel inconsistent to the user.

---

## Token source (`:root` in `styles.css`)

| Variable | Value | Meaning |
|----------|-------|---------|
| `--wb-table-font-size` | `12px` | th and td font-size |
| `--wb-table-cell-padding` | `5px 8px` | th and td padding — compact, matches advertising products list |
| `--wb-table-line-height` | `1.2` | row height baseline (~26px per row) |
| `--wb-table-header-bg` | `#fbf7eb` | sticky header background |
| `--wb-table-body-bg` | `#ffffff` | default td background |
| `--wb-table-totals-bg` | `#fffdf5` | totals / summary row background |
| `--wb-table-sticky-z-col` | `2` | z-index for horizontal sticky columns |
| `--wb-table-sticky-z-header` | `3` | z-index for vertical sticky header |

Do NOT hard-code `12px`, `9px`, `11px`, `#fbf7eb`, or `#ffffff` inside
inline `th`/`td` styles — always reference the CSS variable.

---

## Required table structure

```tsx
// ✅ Correct
<div className="wb-table-wrap--catalog-restricted">   {/* or appropriate wrap */}
  <table className="wb-data-table wb-data-table--products">
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th style={{ width: 60 }}>№</th>          {/* only width inline */}
        <th className="wb-table-cell--sticky-left" style={{ left: 0, width: 120 }}>
          Название
        </th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <td>1</td>
        <td className="wb-table-cell--sticky-left" style={{ left: 0 }}>Товар</td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>
</div>
```

```tsx
// ❌ Wrong — never inline font-size or padding on th/td
<th style={{ fontSize: 11, padding: "6px 8px" }}>Заголовок</th>
<td style={{ fontSize: 12, padding: "9px 11px" }}>Значение</td>
```

---

## Sticky columns/rows — mandatory rules

> **Rule 1 — opaque backgrounds.** Every sticky cell MUST have a solid (non-transparent)
> background. Without this, scrolled content bleeds through the sticky cell.
> Use CSS variables, never hard-code hex colors.

> **Rule 2 — no gap between stacked sticky rows.** When `<thead>` has TWO rows
> (column-header + totals/Итого), the second row MUST add class `wb-thead-row--second`.
> This class sets `top: var(--wb-table-header-row-height)` automatically, keeping both
> sticky rows flush with no visible gap.

> **Rule 3 — z-index ladder.** Never set a custom z-index on a sticky cell outside this ladder:
> - `zIndex: 1` → sticky **td** cells in body rows (use `--wb-table-sticky-z-body-col`)
> - `zIndex: 2` → sticky **th** cells that are only horizontally sticky
> - `zIndex: 3` → vertically sticky header/totals rows (automatic via CSS)
> - `zIndex: 4` → corner cells sticky on both axes
>
> Body sticky `td` cells MUST use `zIndex: 1`, NOT `zIndex: 2`, so they always
> sit BELOW header and totals rows and never "bleed through" them.

### How to apply sticky columns

1. Add class `wb-table-cell--sticky-left` to the `th` or `td`
2. Add `style={{ left: <offset>px }}` for the pixel offset (calculated from column widths)
3. For body `td` cells: use `zIndex: 1` (not 2, 3, or 4)
4. Do NOT set `position: sticky` or `background` inline — the class handles both

### How to apply two stacked sticky header rows

```tsx
<thead>
  {/* Row 1: column headers — top: 0 (automatic via .wb-data-table th) */}
  <tr>
    <th style={{ left: 0 }}>№</th>
    <th>Название</th>
  </tr>
  {/* Row 2: totals/Итого — MUST have wb-thead-row--second for flush stacking */}
  <tr className="wb-products-totals-row wb-thead-row--second">
    <th style={{ left: 0 }} />
    <th>Итого</th>
  </tr>
</thead>
```

`wb-thead-row--second` sets automatically:
- `top: var(--wb-table-header-row-height)` → zero gap below row 1
- `background: var(--wb-table-totals-bg)` → always opaque
- `z-index: var(--wb-table-sticky-z-header)` → above body cells

`wb-table-cell--sticky-left` sets automatically:
- `position: sticky`
- `background: var(--wb-table-body-bg)` for body cells
- `background: var(--wb-table-header-bg)` for header cells
- Correct `z-index` per the ladder above

---

## Allowed inline styles on th/td

| Property | Allowed inline? | Notes |
|----------|-----------------|-------|
| `width` | ✅ | Column widths vary per table |
| `left` | ✅ | Sticky offset only |
| `cursor`, `userSelect` | ✅ | Sortable headers |
| `minWidth`, `maxWidth` | ✅ | Overflow/truncation |
| `textAlign` | ✅ if deviates | Prefer `.wb-table-cell--numeric` for numbers |
| `fontVariantNumeric` | ✅ | Tabular nums for numbers |
| `fontSize` | ❌ | Use CSS variable |
| `padding` | ❌ | Use CSS variable |
| `background` | ❌ for sticky | Use `.wb-table-cell--sticky-left` class |
| `borderBottom` | ❌ | Handled globally |
| `verticalAlign` | ❌ | Handled globally |

---

## Class cheat sheet

| Class | Use case |
|-------|----------|
| `wb-data-table` | Base — every table must have this |
| `wb-data-table--products` | Products / matrix tables (catalog, orders, JAM, cost) |
| `wb-data-table--compact` | Raw WB export tables (9px, minimal padding) |
| `wb-data-table--product-sheet wb-data-table--advertising` | Advertising cluster table (7px, dense) |
| `wb-table-cell--numeric` | Center-align + tabular nums for numeric columns |
| `wb-table-cell--sticky-left` | **Mandatory for every sticky column cell** |
| `wb-products-totals-row` | Summary/totals row (special background) |

---

## What NOT to do

- Do NOT use `RawTableSection.styles.ts` `thStyle`/`tdStyle` to override font/padding
- Do NOT use `position: sticky` inline without `wb-table-cell--sticky-left`
- Do NOT add new `--compact` or `--advertising` modifiers without a strong reason
- Do NOT create a new CSS file for table styles — everything goes in `styles.css`

---

## Enforcement

This rule is evaluated whenever a PR touches files matching:
- `Frontend/src/features/dashboard/**/*.tsx`
- `Frontend/src/styles.css`
- `Frontend/src/features/dashboard/**/*.styles.ts`
